#  prolific game/language designer with 25+ years of game dev).
#  aardappel/lobster: 2,723 GH stars.  Lobster is a STATICALLY-
#  TYPED COMPILED game programming language designed specifically
#  for the game-development use case — not a generic systems
#  language that ALSO happens to do games, but a language whose
#  DESIGN PRIORITIES (fast prototyping, painless visual coordinate
#  systems, built-in graphics/audio/input primitives) are
#  game-development-first.  Compiles to BYTECODE (default) or
#  C++ (`--cpp` flag) or LPAK (Lobster Pack — single-file deploy
#  format with embedded resources).  Compiler ALSO ships an
#  EMBEDDED SDL2 + OpenGL game engine — Lobster programs can
#  directly call `gl.* / camera.* / vec.* / im.* (immediate-mode
#  GUI)` builtins for graphics without external dependencies.
#  Used for hobby/indie game development.  Distinct from other
#  game-scripting: Lua/Wren/Squirrel are EMBEDDED scripting
#  languages designed to be hosted by C/C++ game engines;
#  Lobster is a STANDALONE compiled language with the engine
#  embedded in the compiler instead.  Sister tools: lua (in
#  corpus + STOCK), squirrel (Squirrel embedded scripting),
#  wren_cli (Wren — in corpus via _wren_cli), python (in corpus
#  + STOCK; pygame), love2d (Lua game framework — in corpus via
#  _love), godot (in corpus + STOCK gaming distros — Godot
#  GDScript), pico8 (Pico-8 fantasy console), tic80 (TIC-80
#  fantasy console), defold (Defold engine).
#
#  CLI library taxonomy update: 1st Lobster CLI library —
#  Lobster's **HAND-ROLLED C++ STRCMP-CHAIN PARSER** in
#  `dev/src/main.cpp` `int main(int argc, char* argv[])`.
