#  This pattern is COMMON for SINGLE-DEVELOPER hobby languages and
#  game engines where the CLI surface is small enough that
#  pulling in a library would be over-engineering for a one-
#  person hobby project.  Lobster's hand-rolled approach gives:
#  (a) NO DEPENDENCY on a CLI library — keeps the project's
#  third-party-deps footprint minimal; (b) HAND-MAINTAINED
#  USAGE STRING in the `helptext` C++ string literal that
#  describes every flag in a docstring-style format printed by
#  `--help`; (c) FLEXIBILITY for unusual flag patterns like
#  `--query QUERY_ARGS...` that consumes 4+ following positional
#  values (impossible to express cleanly in most CLI libraries).
#
#  Lobster hand-rolled parser distinctive features:
#    - DOUBLE-DASH LONG FLAGS ONLY — no short flags (-h is NOT
#      registered; `--help` is the only help form), no `--name=
#      value` syntax (use `--name VALUE` with space-separated
#      values)
#    - SPECIAL-CASED MACOS `-psn_` flag — when running as a .app
#      bundle on macOS, the system passes `-psn_NUMBER` as the
#      first arg; Lobster's parser detects the `-psn_` prefix
#      and sets `from_bundle = true` to skip GUI-vs-CLI mode
#      detection
#    - `--` SEPARATOR — terminates option parsing; remaining
#      args become `program_args` accessible from Lobster code
#      via `command_line_arguments()` builtin
#    - VARIADIC `--query` FLAG — consumes 4 mandatory positional
#      values (kind, file, line, iden) plus any remaining args
#      (used by the Lobster Language Server Protocol
#      implementation to query symbol info; powers IDE
#      completion/jump-to-def features)
#    - CONDITIONAL COMPILATION via `#if LOBSTER_ENGINE` — some
#      flags (`--non-interactive-test`) only available in
#      builds with the SDL2 game engine compiled in; build
#      variant `LOBSTER_ENGINE=0` strips them from the parser
#      and help text
#    - PLATFORM-CONDITIONAL via `#ifdef _MSC_VER` — Windows-only
#      `--noconsole` flag for closing the spawned console window
#      after launching from explorer.exe
#    - HAND-MAINTAINED USAGE STRING in the `helptext` C++
#      multi-line string literal — flag descriptions
#      hand-aligned with `--flag      DESCRIPTION` two-column
#      format (24-char left col)
#    - NO env-var fallback (config is purely from argv)
#    - NO subcommand framework (single executable with flags
#      then positional source file then optional `-- program-args`)
#  Lobster's hand-rolled parser philosophy is shared with R424
#  Picat (hand-rolled C parser), R425 BQN (hand-rolled C parser),
#  and many other single-developer / academic / hobby language
#  implementations.  Lobster is the FIRST DOCUMENTED Lobster CLI
#  library in the corpus's cross-language taxonomy.  Lobster
#  joins the 36 other documented languages (Rust, Go, TypeScript-
#  Node, Python, Ruby, Perl, Haskell, OCaml, Elixir, R, Bash,
#  Deno, Lua, Scheme, Clojure, Common Lisp, Racket, Crystal, Nim,
#  Zig, Odin, V, Mojo, Roc, Hare, Standard ML, Erlang, Pony,
#  Prolog, Pike, F#, Janet, D, Picat, BQN, Frege) as the 37th
#  represented language.  Brings cross-language CLI library
#  taxonomy variant count to 175 (174 + hand-rolled-Lobster =
#  175).
#
#  Surface (verbatim from `dev/src/main.cpp` `helptext` string +
#  strcmp chain in main):
#
#  Usage:
#    lobster [ OPTIONS ] [ FILE ] [ -- ARGS ]
#
#  Behavior:
#    Compile & run FILE (if a Lobster source file is given), or
#    omit FILE to load default.lpak (an LPAK pack file in the
#    current directory).  Arguments after `--` are passed to the
#    Lobster program as command_line_arguments().
#
#  Output mode:
#    --cpp                          Compile to C++ code (don't
#                                   run; see implementation.md
#                                   for codegen details)
#    --pak                          Generate lpak file (don't
#                                   run; lpak is Lobster's
#                                   single-file deploy format)
#    --rpak                         Generate lpak file with
#                                   runnable code included
#                                   (don't run)
#    --tcc-out                      Output a tcc .o file instead
#                                   of running (uses TinyCC
#                                   backend for fast compile)
#    --compile-only                 Compile only (don't run);
#                                   useful for syntax checking
#
#  Compilation flow:
#    --import RELDIR                Additional directory (relative
#                                   to FILE) to load imports from
#    --main MAIN                    If present, run this main
#                                   program file after compiling
#                                   FILE (useful for testing
#                                   modules in isolation)
#
#  Diagnostic output:
#    --parsedump                    Also dump parse tree
#    --verbose                      Output additional info text
#    --debug                        Output compiler internal
#                                   logging
#    --silent                       Only output errors (suppress
#                                   info/warnings)
#    --full-error                   Output full compile-time
#                                   stack traces, also for
#                                   warnings
#    --invert-stacktraces           Show stack traces with most
#                                   recent call last (Python
#                                   ordering vs default
#                                   most-recent-first)
#    --errors N                     Output up to N errors
#                                   (default: 1; max 100)
#
#  Runtime checks (mutex group — pick one):
#    --runtime-no-asserts           Compile with asserts OFF
#    --runtime-asserts              Compile with asserts ON
#                                   (default)
#    --runtime-stack-traces         Asserts ON + code locations
#                                   + stack traces
#    --runtime-debug                Also minimize inlining
#    --runtime-debug-dump           Also create debug dumps
#    --runtime-debugger             Also break into debugger on
#                                   error
#    --runtime-debugger-dump        Also create dump + break into
#                                   debugger on error
#
#  Builtin introspection:
#    --gen-builtins-json            Write builtin commands help
#                                   to JSON file
#    --gen-builtins-html            Write builtin commands help
#                                   to HTML file
#    --gen-builtins-html-ng         Write next-gen builtin
#                                   commands HTML file (richer
#                                   format)
#    --gen-builtins-names           Write just the builtin
#                                   command names (no
#                                   descriptions)
#
#  Platform-specific:
#    --noconsole                    Close console window
#                                   (Windows only)
#    --non-interactive-test         Quit after running 1 frame
#                                   (LOBSTER_ENGINE builds only;
#                                   for headless CI testing of
#                                   game programs)
#
#  Interactive / IDE integration:
#    --wait                         Wait for input before exiting
#                                   (useful for double-click
#                                   launches that would close the
#                                   window immediately)
#    --query QUERY_ARGS             Query language server protocol
#                                   for definitions in the program
#                                   being compiled.  QUERY_ARGS is
#                                   4+ values: KIND FILE LINE
#                                   IDENT [extra...].  Powers IDE
#                                   completion / jump-to-def
#                                   features.
#
#  Meta:
#    --help                         Print this help text and exit
#
#  Positional:
#    FILE                           Lobster source file (.lobster
#                                   extension; conventional but
#                                   not enforced) to compile and
#                                   run.  Optional — if omitted,
#                                   loads default.lpak from CWD
#                                   (Lobster Pack file).
#    --                             Separator — everything after
#                                   becomes the Lobster program's
#                                   `command_line_arguments()`
#    ARGS...                        Arguments passed to the
#                                   Lobster program (accessible
#                                   via `command_line_arguments()`
#                                   builtin from Lobster code)
#
#  Examples:
#    lobster game.lobster                              # Compile & run
#    lobster --cpp game.lobster                        # Generate C++ code
#    lobster --pak game.lobster                        # Generate .lpak deploy file
#    lobster --rpak game.lobster                       # Generate runnable .lpak
#    lobster --compile-only game.lobster               # Syntax check only
#    lobster --verbose game.lobster                    # Verbose compile output
#    lobster --silent game.lobster                     # Errors only
#    lobster --runtime-debug game.lobster              # Debug build
#    lobster --runtime-stack-traces game.lobster       # Asserts + stack traces
#    lobster --main app.lobster lib.lobster            # Compile lib but run app
#    lobster --import ./extra/ main.lobster            # Add extra/ to import path
#    lobster --errors 10 game.lobster                  # Show up to 10 errors
#    lobster game.lobster -- arg1 arg2                 # Pass arg1/arg2 to game
#    lobster                                           # Load default.lpak from CWD
#    lobster --gen-builtins-html                       # Write builtin docs HTML
#    lobster --wait game.lobster                       # Wait for keypress before exit
#    lobster --help                                    # Print help
#
#  Dup-skipped neighbors during hunt (in corpus or smaller user base,
#  similar hand-rolled C++ parsers):
#    - lua (IN CORPUS + STOCK Lua interpreter; hand-rolled C
#      parser; FUTURE candidate for Lua formal-library entry)
#    - wren_cli (IN CORPUS via _wren_cli — Wren scripting; hand-
#      rolled parser; FUTURE candidate for Wren formal-language
#      entry)
#    - squirrel (Squirrel embedded scripting; not in corpus)
#    - love2d (IN CORPUS via _love — uses Lua interpreter)
#    - godot (IN CORPUS — Godot GDScript; uses its own parser)
#    - pico8 / tic80 / defold — game fantasy consoles / engines;
#      various states of CLI accessibility
# ============================================================================

_lobster() {
  local context state state_descr line
  typeset -A opt_args

  _arguments -s -S \
    '--help[print this help text and exit]' \
    '--cpp[compile to C++ code (do not run)]' \
    '--pak[generate lpak file (do not run)]' \
    '--rpak[generate lpak file with runnable code (do not run)]' \
    '--tcc-out[output tcc .o file instead of running]' \
    '--compile-only[compile only (do not run)]' \
    '--import=[additional directory (relative to FILE) to load imports from]:dir:_directories' \
    '--main=[run this main program file after compiling FILE]:file:_files -g "*.lobster"' \
    '--parsedump[also dump parse tree]' \
    '--verbose[output additional informational text]' \
    '--debug[output compiler internal logging]' \
    '--silent[only output errors]' \
    '--full-error[output full compile-time stack traces also for warnings]' \
    '--invert-stacktraces[shows stack traces with most recent call last (Python ordering)]' \
    '--errors=[output up to N errors (default 1, max 100)]:n:' \
    '--runtime-no-asserts[compile with asserts off]' \
    '--runtime-asserts[compile with asserts on (default)]' \
    '--runtime-stack-traces[asserts on + code locations + stack traces]' \
    '--runtime-debug[also minimize inlining]' \
    '--runtime-debug-dump[also create debug dumps]' \
    '--runtime-debugger[also break into debugger on error]' \
    '--runtime-debugger-dump[also create dump + break into debugger on error]' \
    '--gen-builtins-json[write builtin commands help to JSON]' \
    '--gen-builtins-html[write builtin commands help to HTML]' \
    '--gen-builtins-html-ng[write next-gen builtin commands HTML]' \
    '--gen-builtins-names[write just the builtin command names]' \
    '--noconsole[close console window (Windows only)]' \
    '--non-interactive-test[quit after running 1 frame (engine builds only)]' \
    '--wait[wait for input before exiting]' \
    '--query[query language server for definitions]:kind:' \
    '*:file:_files -g "*.(lobster|lpak)"'
}

_lobster "$@"
